author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: N.J. burlesque artist drowns on beach in El Salvador
text:
facebook Jessica Paikarovski, 33, died Friday when a wave swept up two people in El Salvador, officials said. The New Jersey burlesque artist started her own show and her own photography and graphic design company, according to her LinkedIn profile. A New Jersey burlesque artist drowned Friday when a wave swept her and another person into the Pacific Ocean at a private beach in El Salvador, officials said.
Jessica Paikarovski, 33, died after the crest on El Majahual Beach in the popular tourist area of La Libertad, according to a statement by the country’s General Prosecutor .
Paikarovski, who often went by her stage name “Jess Distress,” had been traveling with a ska band and was sitting by a pool with one of the band members when the wave hit, her sister told NJ Advance Media .
“The pool relied on ocean water to fill it up,” said Ann Paikarovski. “A wave came over them and sucked them under.”
